instruction:
Sometimes you need more than a message. You want a structured error you can inspect programmatically.

Create a custom error type by defining a struct with an `Error() string` method:

```
type LibraryError struct {
    Code    string
    Message string
}

func (e LibraryError) Error() string {
    return fmt.Sprintf("[%s] %s", e.Code, e.Message)
}
```

Run this and see the custom error printed. Then add a second return that returns a `LibraryError` for the `"OVERDUE"` code.

